snippet: The outcome seemed to give Ron Paul, often dismissed as a protest candidate, reason to extend his campaign.
abstract: Republican presidential hopeful Ron Paul finishes a strong second in New Hampshire primary, which in many ways is the more telling outcome in a race where Mitt Romney's dominance was never in doubt; outcome seems to give Paul, often dismissed as a protest candidate, reason to extend his campaign.

byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Richard A. Oppel Jr. in Leesville, S.C., and Katharine Q. Seelye, Marjorie Connelly and Michael D. Shear in Manchester.

lead_paragraph: The outcome seemed to give Ron Paul, often dismissed as a protest candidate, reason to extend his campaign.

headline.main: Ron Paul Finishes Second in New Hampshire
headline.print_headline: A Victory, of Sorts, for Second-Place Finisher Paul in New Hampshire
